WEBVTT

00:03.174 --> 00:03.924
Previously on
"Grey's Anatomy"...

00:03.924 --> 00:05.386
I love you.

00:05.386 --> 00:06.887
I love everything about you.

00:06.887 --> 00:08.929
I get to change lives!
That's the dream!

00:08.929 --> 00:10.261
Fine, I don't want
to go to Africa.

00:10.261 --> 00:12.803
I found out that
I'm pregnant with Mark's baby.

00:12.803 --> 00:14.095
Are you in
or are you out?

00:14.095 --> 00:14.845
I'm in.

00:14.845 --> 00:16.016
Oh, my God!

00:16.016 --> 00:17.898
[ Gasps ] Callie!
Callie!

00:17.898 --> 00:20.901
[ Monitor beeps ]

00:20.901 --> 00:23.944
Callie: I choose you to be the
one with whom I spend my life.

00:23.944 --> 00:24.985
[ Gasps ]

00:24.985 --> 00:26.737
I can't keep doing this
alone, Arizona.

00:26.737 --> 00:29.280
[ Cries ]

00:29.280 --> 00:30.651
Arizona: I thought we were past
the hard stuff.

00:30.651 --> 00:32.413
-We have a child!
-I know!

00:32.413 --> 00:34.995
How could you do this?
I don't want to fix us anymore.

00:35.616 --> 00:36.827
This is Penny.

00:36.827 --> 00:37.998
Arizona:
Callie's moving to New York.

00:37.998 --> 00:39.290
And she's trying
to take Sofia with her.

00:39.290 --> 00:41.832
-You hired a lawyer.
-You started this.

00:43.003 --> 00:45.796
♪♪

00:48.379 --> 00:50.721
Meredith:
There's this Bible story.

00:50.721 --> 00:54.595
Two women both claim to be
the mother of the same child.

00:54.595 --> 00:57.228
Gamble: My client is prepared to
offer scheduled visitation

00:57.228 --> 00:58.729
every other weekend.

00:58.729 --> 01:00.231
King Solomon had to choose.

01:00.231 --> 01:01.602
That is ridiculous,
and she knows it.

01:01.602 --> 01:04.235
Sofia cannot take a six-hour
flight by herself twice a month.

01:04.235 --> 01:05.316
That would be a hard no.

01:05.316 --> 01:06.487
Hold, please.

01:06.487 --> 01:08.319
Two mothers.
Only one gets the kid.

01:08.319 --> 01:09.740
We knew
they'd shoot that down.

01:09.740 --> 01:10.821
They are
shooting everything down

01:10.821 --> 01:12.533
because they're being
unreasonable.

01:12.533 --> 01:14.615
They have the luxury of being
unreasonable right now.

01:14.615 --> 01:16.657
We have less than 12 hours
to try to settle.

01:16.657 --> 01:18.619
Their witness lineup is better,
and they know it.

01:18.619 --> 01:19.870
We have Richard Webber.

01:22.253 --> 01:24.125
S-- Ok--

01:24.125 --> 01:26.297
Maybe we should put April
on the stand.
Kepner? No.

01:26.297 --> 01:28.419
We're not calling a witness
you just fired as a patient.

01:28.419 --> 01:30.921
But she's seen me with Sofia
more than anyone,

01:30.921 --> 01:32.383
and she's a good person.
She'll tell the truth.

01:32.383 --> 01:33.764
No, she's a wild card.
It's too risky.

01:35.516 --> 01:36.597
Webber's good.

01:36.597 --> 01:38.389
He better be.

01:38.389 --> 01:41.602
What is your client prepared
to offer as an alternative?

01:41.602 --> 01:45.526
Solomon came up with a plan.
He proposed a 50/50 split.

01:45.526 --> 01:47.228
Visitation rights
for Dr. Robbins

01:47.228 --> 01:49.029
on school breaks
and summers.

01:49.029 --> 01:50.441
That puts us right back
where we started.

01:50.441 --> 01:52.733
Literally. He offered to
chop the kid in half.

01:52.733 --> 01:54.285
It's a reasonable compromise.

01:54.285 --> 01:55.616
Yeah, well, you can take your
compromise

01:55.616 --> 01:56.577
and shove it up your --
-Oh, no. You know what?

01:56.577 --> 01:57.828
You can --

01:57.828 --> 01:59.290
Gamble:
Arizona, look at me.

01:59.290 --> 02:01.121
We are at an impasse here.

02:01.121 --> 02:03.003
If we don't settle,
if we go to trial,

02:03.003 --> 02:04.915
you risk losing it all.

02:04.915 --> 02:08.339
Only one of you is walking out
of that court with sole custody.

02:08.339 --> 02:11.382
I am painfully aware
of that.

02:11.382 --> 02:13.384
Then I urge you to consider
their offer.

02:13.384 --> 02:14.885
Their offer is insulting.

02:17.388 --> 02:19.430
And last time I checked,
you work for me.

02:20.851 --> 02:21.852
[ Phone beeps ]

02:21.852 --> 02:24.265
-That would be a hard no.
-Hold.

02:24.265 --> 02:27.067
It all ends if one mom
relinquishes her custody.

02:30.191 --> 02:32.363
[ Phone beeps ]

02:32.363 --> 02:33.534
Gamble.

02:33.534 --> 02:35.276
We're here.

02:35.276 --> 02:37.278
Or else they both
stand their ground.

02:37.278 --> 02:40.331
♪♪

02:43.874 --> 02:45.666
[ Sighs ]

02:50.090 --> 02:51.712
We'll see you in court.

02:51.712 --> 02:54.885
And the kid gets torn apart.

03:07.688 --> 03:10.611
[ Alarm beeps ]

03:10.611 --> 03:12.733
[ Sighs ]

03:15.616 --> 03:17.408
[ Doorbell rings ]

03:18.909 --> 03:20.531
[ Door opens ]

03:20.531 --> 03:21.582
Hi, Sofia!

03:21.582 --> 03:22.873
[ Giggles ]

03:22.873 --> 03:25.416
Mer will be down
in a second.

03:25.416 --> 03:27.248
I'm so sorry about this.

03:27.248 --> 03:29.460
Please. It's the best way
to spend a day off.

03:29.460 --> 03:31.332
[ Laughs ]

03:31.332 --> 03:33.674
Hey, I'm thinking
pancakes for breakfast.

03:33.674 --> 03:34.925
With chocolate chips?

03:34.925 --> 03:36.216
-Ooh.
-Crazytown!

03:36.216 --> 03:37.468
Let's do it.

03:37.468 --> 03:38.218
[ Laughter ]

03:38.218 --> 03:39.600
[ Dog barking in distance ]

03:39.600 --> 03:41.892
Does, um, Sofia know
anything about

03:41.892 --> 03:44.184
what her mommies are doing
today?
Nope.

03:44.184 --> 03:46.517
We're gonna talk to her after we
know exactly what's happening.

03:46.517 --> 03:48.309
Hey. You ready?

03:48.309 --> 03:50.481
[ Sighs ]

03:50.481 --> 03:52.483
[ Birds chirping ]

03:53.904 --> 03:55.155
Hey. Come here.

03:55.155 --> 03:58.359
Come here.
Oh, I'm gonna miss you so much.

03:58.359 --> 04:00.200
You know what?

04:00.200 --> 04:03.033
Mama loves you so, so much.

04:04.204 --> 04:06.206
I will see you again
before you know it.

04:06.206 --> 04:07.998
I know.

04:10.581 --> 04:12.583
You're hugging me too tight.

04:12.583 --> 04:14.505
[ Sniffles ]

04:16.717 --> 04:18.258
You're hugging me too long.

04:19.840 --> 04:23.053
Callie, we have to go.
We don't want to be late.

04:23.053 --> 04:24.685
Come on. Come on.

04:24.685 --> 04:26.186
Come on. Come on.

04:26.186 --> 04:27.187
Okay.

04:27.187 --> 04:28.439
Hey.
Let's go find Zola!

04:31.312 --> 04:32.483
[ Sighs ]

04:32.483 --> 04:33.984
Hey.

04:33.984 --> 04:35.566
She's gonna be fine.

04:35.566 --> 04:37.107
She's with Maggie.
Okay, come on.

04:37.107 --> 04:38.198
Come on.

04:38.198 --> 04:39.820
It's gonna be okay.

04:39.820 --> 04:42.663
♪♪

04:42.663 --> 04:44.575
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:45.906 --> 04:47.788
This one is deeper
than I would like.

04:47.788 --> 04:49.460
I'll stitch it up.
You have to go.

04:49.460 --> 04:50.501
Is the baby okay?

04:50.501 --> 04:52.583
Let's take a look.

04:52.583 --> 04:54.965
April: Jenny? Hi, Tara.

04:54.965 --> 04:57.217
-I heard you fell.
-On some dishes.

04:57.217 --> 04:59.630
I was washing them and got
soapy water all over the floor.

04:59.630 --> 05:00.881
Then I slipped.

05:00.881 --> 05:02.633
I told her
I would do them later.

05:02.633 --> 05:03.724
She's nesting, I think.

05:03.724 --> 05:05.305
[ Scoffs ]
Mom, cut it out.

05:05.305 --> 05:08.308
There is the baby's heartbeat --
nice and steady --

05:08.308 --> 05:10.351
and the baby's active,
which is exactly what you want.

05:10.351 --> 05:12.142
I fell really hard.
Are you sure?

05:12.142 --> 05:13.273
Well, the baby looks great,

05:13.273 --> 05:15.105
but I see some free fluid
in your abdomen.

05:15.105 --> 05:16.777
It might be bleeding.
-Or amniotic fluid.

05:16.777 --> 05:18.238
[ Sighs ] Jenny, I'm gonna have
to take you up and have a look.

05:18.238 --> 05:20.110
-Surgery?
-No.

05:20.110 --> 05:22.152
No surgery. I don't want to
go through that again.

05:22.152 --> 05:23.864
It's nothing.
I'm gonna make a small incision,

05:23.864 --> 05:25.706
put a scope in there, make sure
everything's all right.

05:25.706 --> 05:27.618
You'll be there, right?

05:27.618 --> 05:29.079
Um, I'm -- I'm sorry.

05:29.079 --> 05:31.502
Actually, I wish I could.
Today I can't.

05:31.502 --> 05:33.163
Dr. Russo
will monitor the baby.

05:33.163 --> 05:34.835
He's the OB on call,
and he's great.

05:34.835 --> 05:36.126
I will be there, though.
I'm happy to.

05:36.126 --> 05:37.297
Don't you need to get going?

05:37.297 --> 05:39.670
Yeah.
Um, I will check in later.

05:39.670 --> 05:42.172
Um, Russo's good,
but he can be

05:42.172 --> 05:43.223
a little old-school,
just so you know.

05:43.223 --> 05:45.846
-All right. Go.
-Okay.

05:45.846 --> 05:47.728
I can't believe you dumped Kyle
with a note.

05:47.728 --> 05:48.849
Brutal.

05:48.849 --> 05:50.391
Yeah,
not my finest moment.

05:50.391 --> 05:53.894
That's like dumping someone
by text, only in 1980.

05:53.894 --> 05:55.606
Remind me why you broke up
with him at all?

05:55.606 --> 05:56.777
-You know why.
-I know.

05:56.777 --> 05:58.859
It's just that he's so hot

05:58.859 --> 06:01.361
and he's into you
and he plays guitar,

06:01.361 --> 06:04.114
and he's sick,
so you always know where he is.

06:04.114 --> 06:05.446
-Wow.
-I know.

06:05.446 --> 06:07.578
You had to choose between
doctor and girlfriend.

06:07.578 --> 06:08.368
You made the right choice.

06:08.368 --> 06:09.950
Thank you.

06:09.950 --> 06:13.083
However, there are countless
other brains to cut into

06:13.083 --> 06:15.335
but a limited number of butts
like his.

06:15.335 --> 06:16.667
Keep your eyes
on your own butt.

06:16.667 --> 06:18.168
[ Elevator bell dings ]

06:18.168 --> 06:19.590
[ Indistinct conversations ]

06:19.590 --> 06:21.712
[ Horns honk ]

06:21.712 --> 06:23.383
Arizona: [ Sniffles ]

06:23.383 --> 06:25.005
Hey.

06:25.005 --> 06:27.638
Well, I, uh,
ground the beans myself.

06:27.638 --> 06:29.059
Thanks. Let's go.

06:29.059 --> 06:30.220
Wait, wait.

06:30.220 --> 06:31.602
We have a few minutes.

06:31.602 --> 06:33.143
How you feeling?

06:33.143 --> 06:34.435
[ Sighs ]

06:34.435 --> 06:36.687
Robbins.

06:36.687 --> 06:39.319
It'll be tough, but right now,
you have to look past the pain

06:39.319 --> 06:41.281
to what you'll have
when they're done.

06:41.281 --> 06:43.323
"At the end,
you'll have a baby."

06:43.323 --> 06:45.025
That's what I tell
all the laboring moms.

06:45.025 --> 06:46.697
[ Chuckles ]

06:46.697 --> 06:48.158
You're not drinking.

06:48.158 --> 06:49.910
Oh. Okay.

06:49.910 --> 06:51.241
[ Indistinct conversations ]

06:51.241 --> 06:52.993
[ Horns honk ]

06:56.246 --> 06:58.168
Judge Kane:
We're here today to determine

06:58.168 --> 07:00.501
a custody modification
of a minor

07:00.501 --> 07:02.963
between two divorced parents,

07:02.963 --> 07:06.847
Arizona Robbins
and Calliope Torres.

07:06.847 --> 07:10.931
The trial's witness pool
is unusual

07:10.931 --> 07:13.974
in that it'll be shared
by both parents.

07:13.974 --> 07:17.357
The parties have stipulated
to call each witness once,

07:17.357 --> 07:18.819
at which time,

07:18.819 --> 07:21.862
each side will have a chance
to examine that witness.

07:22.402 --> 07:23.694
[ Door closes ]

07:23.694 --> 07:25.115
If you're testifying,
remember --

07:25.115 --> 07:27.157
this is not
a popularity contest.

07:27.157 --> 07:29.530
You are not choosing sides.

07:29.530 --> 07:31.742
We're all on the same side --

07:31.742 --> 07:34.625
the side of a 6-year-old child.

07:34.625 --> 07:37.417
Dr. Torres, Dr. Robbins,

07:37.417 --> 07:40.130
custody hearings are,
without exception,

07:40.130 --> 07:42.633
very difficult
on all parties involved,

07:42.633 --> 07:44.004
your daughter included.

07:44.004 --> 07:47.508
Things said here
will undoubtedly be harsh

07:47.508 --> 07:49.299
and cannot be unsaid.

07:49.299 --> 07:53.764
I ask this of parents before
I begin any custody hearing.

07:53.764 --> 07:55.896
Are you both sure
you want to proceed?

07:59.189 --> 08:00.811
Yes, Your Honor.
I'm sure.

08:02.402 --> 08:04.525
Dr. Torres.

08:04.525 --> 08:06.907
I'm sure, Your Honor.

08:06.907 --> 08:08.448
Then this court
is now in session

08:08.448 --> 08:10.741
to determine
sole physical custody

08:10.741 --> 08:13.243
of Sofia Robbin Sloan Torres.

08:22.923 --> 08:24.084
Dr. Torres and I worked together
on a pro bono project

08:24.084 --> 08:26.046
building prosthetics
for injured vets.

08:26.046 --> 08:28.048
And that's a very meaningful
project for you

08:28.048 --> 08:29.630
because
you're a vet yourself.

08:29.630 --> 08:31.011
Is that correct?

08:31.011 --> 08:32.763
Yes, I served as a surgeon
in the Army.

08:34.935 --> 08:36.897
Charity work
and the vet card.

08:36.897 --> 08:38.058
That's smart.

08:38.058 --> 08:39.640
Yeah,
it's not good for Robbins.

08:39.640 --> 08:41.562
Carpio: What was the connection
for Dr. Torres?

08:41.562 --> 08:43.564
Well, she just cares.

08:43.564 --> 08:44.775
While she didn't serve,

08:44.775 --> 08:47.608
she's always been willing
to pitch in, to help.

08:47.608 --> 08:49.860
She's a very empathetic person.

08:49.860 --> 08:51.491
Big-hearted.

08:51.491 --> 08:54.454
Has Dr. Torres discussed
her move to New York with you?

08:54.454 --> 08:56.867
She has.
Did you feel it was
a sudden move?

08:56.867 --> 08:59.329
Um, well, not for her.
I mean, it was sudden

08:59.329 --> 09:00.961
because Dr. Blake's schedule
determined the move,

09:00.961 --> 09:02.252
but for Callie, no.

09:02.252 --> 09:03.664
This is who she is.

09:03.664 --> 09:05.465
She gets thrown a situation --
it doesn't daunt her.

09:05.465 --> 09:07.047
It inspires her.

09:07.047 --> 09:08.428
I've seen it time and time again
in the O.R.

09:08.428 --> 09:10.050
She just jumps in.

09:10.050 --> 09:11.131
And this is no different.

09:11.131 --> 09:13.634
She's found a great school
for Sofia,

09:13.634 --> 09:18.518
and she's making the best of
a tough situation with grace.

09:18.518 --> 09:20.771
It's something
I admire about her.

09:25.946 --> 09:27.778
No further questions
at this time.

09:31.692 --> 09:35.786
You live with Dr. Robbins,
don't you?

09:35.786 --> 09:38.328
I rent a room in her house.

09:38.328 --> 09:42.122
I bet you never expected
to be living with a 6-year-old.

09:42.122 --> 09:43.794
Yeah, sure.
I wasn't, uh, thrilled

09:43.794 --> 09:45.796
to be living
with a kid, uh,

09:45.796 --> 09:48.338
till I started
living with one.

09:48.338 --> 09:50.260
I had never been around
a lot of kids before,

09:50.260 --> 09:51.672
but Sofia's a blast.

09:51.672 --> 09:54.304
She's so smart and hilarious.

09:54.304 --> 09:56.637
I mean, she and her mom
are just laughing all the time.

09:56.637 --> 09:58.218
The place is so happy.

09:58.218 --> 10:01.061
Sofia makes the place happy.

10:01.061 --> 10:04.604
We see so much dark stuff
every day at work.

10:04.604 --> 10:07.527
It's -- It's really nice
to come home to a happy kid.

10:07.527 --> 10:10.070
Mm.

10:10.070 --> 10:14.695
So, would you say
you love Sofia?

10:16.737 --> 10:19.369
I -- I have come to.
Yes.

10:19.369 --> 10:20.911
Oh, that's nice.

10:20.911 --> 10:23.203
And how long have you known
Sofia now?

10:23.203 --> 10:26.166
Well,
we met a few months ago.

10:26.166 --> 10:29.299
Oh, and how well would you say
you've gotten to know Sofia

10:29.299 --> 10:31.962
in the few months that you've
spent together, Dr. Blake?

10:31.962 --> 10:33.463
Very well.

10:33.463 --> 10:35.716
Oh. Very well.
That's good.

10:35.716 --> 10:37.968
That's, uh, very good.

10:37.968 --> 10:39.429
What's her favorite color?

10:39.429 --> 10:40.560
Blue.

10:40.560 --> 10:42.102
Her favorite toy?

10:42.102 --> 10:44.895
Objection. Irrelevant.
This isn't a quiz show.

10:44.895 --> 10:46.606
I'm trying to
establish the nature

10:46.606 --> 10:48.648
of Dr. Blake's relationship
with Sofia.

10:48.648 --> 10:49.940
Judge Kane: I'll allow it.

10:52.232 --> 10:54.614
Her favorite toy
is Astronaut Barbie.

10:54.614 --> 10:56.987
Her favorite cereal
is Whole Grain O's.

10:56.987 --> 10:59.039
Her favorite animal
is a unicorn.

10:59.039 --> 11:02.542
Her favorite sea creature
is a mermaid.

11:02.542 --> 11:04.624
And her bedtime is 8:30.

11:04.624 --> 11:05.836
And her favorite thing to do
in the morning

11:05.836 --> 11:08.048
is pick out her outfit.
[ Chuckles ]

11:08.048 --> 11:10.500
You can ask me
anything you want.

11:13.213 --> 11:14.294
[ Monitor beeping ]

11:14.294 --> 11:17.718
5mm scope.

11:17.718 --> 11:18.849
So, why aren't you there?

11:18.849 --> 11:19.890
In court?

11:19.890 --> 11:21.722
Why aren't you there?

11:21.722 --> 11:23.643
I've seen enough people
fighting over kids.

11:23.643 --> 11:25.015
I've had enough
of fighting over my own,

11:25.015 --> 11:26.566
and mine's not even born yet.

11:26.566 --> 11:28.478
Well,
there's the free fluid.

11:28.478 --> 11:29.770
Suction irrigator, please.

11:29.770 --> 11:31.191
How are we looking here,
Dr. Karev?

11:31.191 --> 11:32.482
Uh, well,
that's not blood.

11:32.482 --> 11:33.904
Ohh. Oh, no.

11:33.904 --> 11:35.776
Looks like amniotic fluid.

11:35.776 --> 11:38.118
Show me the uterine fundus,
please.

11:39.279 --> 11:41.531
[ Sighs ] Damn it.
Uterus is perforated.

11:41.531 --> 11:42.913
Let me have a look there.

11:42.913 --> 11:44.875
Thank you.
[ Sighs ]

11:44.875 --> 11:47.207
Getting fluid
in her abdomen.

11:47.207 --> 11:49.379
This pregnancy has just become
non-viable.

11:49.379 --> 11:51.211
This baby's barely viable
outside that womb.

11:51.211 --> 11:52.502
It's only 24 weeks.

11:52.502 --> 11:54.504
You can repair it,
can't you?
I can try.

11:54.504 --> 11:56.596
Throw in a plasma patch,
hope for the best.

11:56.596 --> 11:58.468
-"Hope for the best?"
-It's experimental,

11:58.468 --> 12:00.220
but if we want to
prolong this pregnancy --

12:00.220 --> 12:02.472
-Of course we do.
-Then a patch is the way to go.

12:02.472 --> 12:04.684
Five seconds ago,
you wanted to deliver.

12:04.684 --> 12:06.016
Now you're confident
in a plasma patch?

12:06.016 --> 12:08.188
Dr. Karev,
I am the OB on call here.

12:08.188 --> 12:09.729
You are a peds surgeon.

12:09.729 --> 12:12.272
If I say that a patch is best,
a patch is best.

12:12.272 --> 12:13.443
Kepner?

12:13.443 --> 12:15.695
If it keeps the baby in,
I vote for the patch.

12:16.947 --> 12:19.159
Stay in your lane,
Dr. Karev.

12:19.159 --> 12:21.491
Prep albumin polymers,
please.

12:21.491 --> 12:24.324
I'll update the mom.

12:24.324 --> 12:26.036
[ Monitor beeps ]

12:26.036 --> 12:28.708
♪♪

12:31.501 --> 12:33.293
[ Monitor beeping ]

12:33.293 --> 12:34.584
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A. system ]

12:34.584 --> 12:36.586
[ Indistinct conversations ]

12:36.586 --> 12:39.009
How'd it go?
How's Jenny?

12:39.009 --> 12:40.760
Well, she's still in surgery
but doing great.

12:40.760 --> 12:42.262
We located
the source of the leak,

12:42.262 --> 12:44.264
and Dr. Russo's repairing it
right now.

12:44.264 --> 12:46.056
And the baby?

12:46.056 --> 12:47.888
The baby is healthy
and still in utero,

12:47.888 --> 12:48.979
which is what we want.

12:48.979 --> 12:49.980
[ Sighs ]

12:49.980 --> 12:51.892
It's too little to be born,
right?

12:51.892 --> 12:54.154
It wouldn't be ideal.

12:54.154 --> 12:58.068
I-I need you to sign one more
form for Dr. Russo's repair.

12:58.068 --> 13:00.030
It seems like
I was just here

13:00.030 --> 13:02.282
signing these
for Jenny's last surgery.

13:03.573 --> 13:05.115
[ Sighs ]

13:05.115 --> 13:07.207
I just had a feeling.

13:07.207 --> 13:08.368
I said goodbye.

13:08.368 --> 13:09.870
I left for work.

13:09.870 --> 13:11.041
I was two blocks away

13:11.041 --> 13:14.674
and I had an awful,
just sick feeling.

13:14.674 --> 13:17.297
I turned around, I drove home,
and there she was --

13:17.297 --> 13:20.130
on the floor,
blood everywhere.

13:20.130 --> 13:21.842
[ Voice breaking ]
I just had a terrible feeling

13:21.842 --> 13:24.264
that something
was really wrong.

13:25.635 --> 13:28.018
It's a good thing you did.

13:28.018 --> 13:30.310
[ Sighs ]

13:30.310 --> 13:33.353
♪♪

13:35.025 --> 13:38.238
And your work schedule will be
pretty grueling, I'd imagine.

13:38.238 --> 13:40.110
Penny: Actually,
it's a research fellowship,

13:40.110 --> 13:42.202
so it will be
far more predictable

13:42.202 --> 13:43.864
than a surgery resident's
schedule.

13:43.864 --> 13:45.946
Oh, I see.

13:45.946 --> 13:47.948
What was Sofia wearing
this morning?

13:47.948 --> 13:49.870
-What?
-What was she wearing today?

13:49.870 --> 13:52.002
I --

13:52.002 --> 13:53.043
I don't know.

13:53.043 --> 13:54.414
You didn't see her
this morning?

13:54.414 --> 13:55.415
No, I-I did.

13:55.415 --> 13:57.047
I just, uh --

13:57.047 --> 13:59.669
I can't, um, recall
exactly what it --

13:59.669 --> 14:01.261
Objection.
Relevance.

14:01.261 --> 14:02.592
Moving on.

14:02.592 --> 14:05.175
What grade is Sofia in?

14:05.175 --> 14:06.386
Second.

14:06.386 --> 14:07.517
No, first.

14:09.349 --> 14:10.430
She's in first grade.

14:11.391 --> 14:14.734
I have to go, and this is
getting hard to watch.

14:14.734 --> 14:16.566
Are you sure?

14:16.566 --> 14:18.398
-Yes.
-Because you didn't sound sure,

14:18.398 --> 14:20.070
and you keep saying this is
a child that you know,

14:20.070 --> 14:23.483
a child that
you're gonna soon co-parent.

14:23.483 --> 14:25.285
I-I-I can see
how you might not remember...
[ Door opens, closes ]

14:25.285 --> 14:27.117
...what color tutu she wore
to school today,

14:27.117 --> 14:29.199
but to not even know
what grade she's in --

14:29.199 --> 14:31.831
So many objections.
Badgering, irrelevant --

14:31.831 --> 14:32.953
-Sustained.
-I'm sorry.

14:32.953 --> 14:34.334
I don't mean to
belabor the point,

14:34.334 --> 14:35.585
but you said it yourself.

14:35.585 --> 14:37.757
You've only known Sofia
a few months, so --

14:37.757 --> 14:39.379
No,
that is not what I meant.

14:39.379 --> 14:41.171
But that is what you said.

14:42.382 --> 14:44.004
All right, Counselor.

14:44.004 --> 14:45.805
I know what grade she's in.

14:45.805 --> 14:47.217
I do.

14:47.217 --> 14:48.268
I do.

14:48.268 --> 14:50.220
No further questions,
Your Honor.

14:50.220 --> 14:53.273
♪♪

15:02.192 --> 15:03.823
[ Clock ticking ]

15:09.869 --> 15:11.911
Maybe it wasn't that bad.
[ Door opens ]

15:11.911 --> 15:14.244
That was
really, really bad.

15:14.244 --> 15:15.956
Oh, God.

15:15.956 --> 15:17.627
[ Sighs ]

15:17.627 --> 15:19.669
But it doesn't kill us.
Not yet.

15:19.669 --> 15:22.132
I can't believe Arizona let them
pull that slimy bull--

15:22.132 --> 15:23.633
It was a smart move,
and it worked.

15:23.633 --> 15:25.095
But we've got smarter moves.

15:25.095 --> 15:26.806
Let me put Dr. Grey on the stand
tomorrow,

15:26.806 --> 15:28.348
and she's gonna close strong.

15:28.348 --> 15:30.050
Look confident.

15:30.050 --> 15:32.472
[ Scoffs ]

15:32.472 --> 15:35.395
Carpio:
You're the Chief of Surgery.

15:35.395 --> 15:37.687
Doctors Torres and Robbins
report to you.

15:37.687 --> 15:39.319
That is correct.

15:39.319 --> 15:41.191
And for those of us
who aren't surgeons,

15:41.191 --> 15:43.113
Dr. Torres operates on bones

15:43.113 --> 15:44.444
while Dr. Robbins
operates on babies.

15:44.444 --> 15:45.695
Is that correct?

15:45.695 --> 15:47.067
Well,
fetuses and babies.

15:47.067 --> 15:48.698
Yes.

15:48.698 --> 15:50.120
How does the schedule
of an orthopedic surgeon

15:50.120 --> 15:51.951
compare to that
of a fetal surgeon?

15:51.951 --> 15:53.623
It varies day to day.

15:53.623 --> 15:55.035
I see,
but in your opinion,

15:55.035 --> 15:58.578
which specialty has more
unscheduled surgeries?

15:58.578 --> 16:01.461
Ortho or fetal?
-There's really no comparison.

16:01.461 --> 16:03.503
But Dr. Robbins' schedule
is dictated

16:03.503 --> 16:05.755
by the unpredictable nature
of childbirth, is it not?

16:05.755 --> 16:07.217
Objection.
Speculation.

16:08.588 --> 16:09.549
She can't do that.

16:09.549 --> 16:10.890
You can't do that.

16:10.890 --> 16:14.224
I asked
if Dr. Robbins' schedule

16:14.224 --> 16:17.437
is dictated by the unpredictable
nature of childbirth.

16:17.437 --> 16:19.229
Objection.
Speculation.

16:19.229 --> 16:22.442
Your Honor, I'm asking
an expert witness her opinion.

16:22.442 --> 16:24.904
It's only speculation if counsel
is calling into question

16:24.904 --> 16:26.566
the expertise of this witness
as Chief.

16:26.566 --> 16:28.368
Overruled.
Counselor, proceed.

16:28.368 --> 16:31.321
Dr. Robbins' schedule is
unpredictable, wouldn't you say?

16:31.321 --> 16:34.704
[ Sighs ]

16:34.704 --> 16:36.616
It can be, yes.
Any surgeon's --

16:36.616 --> 16:39.419
Sure, but how many
unscheduled emergency procedures

16:39.419 --> 16:41.921
did Dr. Robbins log
over the past six months?

16:41.921 --> 16:43.383
I have no idea.

16:43.383 --> 16:45.885
I would like to introduce
into evidence Document 2C.

16:50.800 --> 16:52.892
Take a look.
This might refresh your memory.

16:52.892 --> 16:54.134
What is that report,
Doctor?

16:54.134 --> 16:58.438
This is a list of
emergency procedures performed

16:58.438 --> 17:02.062
by Dr. Robbins and Dr. Torres
for the past six months.

17:02.062 --> 17:02.942
And according to
that document,

17:02.942 --> 17:04.274
how many
emergency procedures

17:04.274 --> 17:07.147
did Dr. Torres log
in the past six months?

17:07.147 --> 17:09.529
Uh...

17:09.529 --> 17:10.530
27.

17:10.530 --> 17:12.652
27.

17:12.652 --> 17:15.034
And how many
did Dr. Robbins log?

17:18.418 --> 17:20.160
[ Clears throat ]

17:20.160 --> 17:21.161
92.

17:21.161 --> 17:23.503
92.

17:23.503 --> 17:25.215
Now, even for a surgeon,

17:25.215 --> 17:26.836
wouldn't you call that kind of
schedule grueling?

17:26.836 --> 17:28.468
You can say that.
I wouldn't.

17:28.468 --> 17:30.800
I would say
it's wildly successful,

17:30.800 --> 17:32.432
but then,
I would never put

17:32.432 --> 17:35.305
a woman's success
in the con column.

17:35.305 --> 17:36.846
What about her daughter,
though?

17:36.846 --> 17:38.178
92.

17:38.178 --> 17:40.770
92 times
she dropped everything,

17:40.770 --> 17:43.683
Sofia included,
to go to a job.

17:43.683 --> 17:46.146
Would you ask that
if she were a man?

17:48.568 --> 17:51.741
92 times she chose work
over her child.

17:51.741 --> 17:53.032
Your Honor --

17:53.032 --> 17:56.156
92 times Dr. Robbins
was saving babies,

17:56.156 --> 17:58.538
saving parents from losing
their own children!

17:58.538 --> 18:01.501
No further questions.

18:03.042 --> 18:04.704
Don't get discouraged.

18:04.704 --> 18:07.257
They're trying to turn
your strength into weakness.

18:07.257 --> 18:08.338
[ Sighs ]

18:08.338 --> 18:10.510
♪♪

18:10.510 --> 18:13.343
This court is adjourned
until tomorrow.

18:13.343 --> 18:16.136
♪♪

18:19.479 --> 18:20.520
[ Siren wailing ]

18:20.520 --> 18:21.521
Tara: No, over here.

18:21.521 --> 18:22.642
Right up against the bed.

18:22.642 --> 18:24.774
God, Mom.
Just go home to sleep.

18:24.774 --> 18:26.646
This is so embarrassing.

18:26.646 --> 18:28.398
I'm sorry.
She's a nightmare.

18:28.398 --> 18:31.070
That's right.
I'm everybody's nightmare.

18:31.070 --> 18:32.692
Can I have another blanket,
please?
Sure.

18:32.692 --> 18:33.733
Hey!

18:33.733 --> 18:34.944
How's everyone feeling?

18:34.944 --> 18:36.035
I hear you're sleeping over
tonight.

18:36.035 --> 18:37.157
Thank God you're back.

18:37.157 --> 18:38.618
She's nicer to me
when you're around.

18:38.618 --> 18:40.410
[ Laughs ]
Surgery went well?

18:40.410 --> 18:42.202
Yeah.
Russo did a plasma patch.

18:42.202 --> 18:45.335
Yeah, that's a good call.
This baby needs more time.

18:45.335 --> 18:47.377
Okay, listen. I'm sorry that
I wasn't here for the surgery,

18:47.377 --> 18:50.089
but I'll be checking in later,
okay?

18:51.301 --> 18:52.172
[ Monitor beeps ]

18:52.172 --> 18:53.713
[ Sighs ]

18:53.713 --> 18:55.755
I told you.
Kepner and I have Jenny handled.

18:55.755 --> 18:57.217
She's doing fine.
The baby's good.

18:57.217 --> 18:59.018
Everyone's stable.
-Um, where's Russo?

18:59.018 --> 19:00.220
I need to look at
a post-op ultrasound

19:00.220 --> 19:02.352
to make sure the leak is sealed.
-Should you be here?

19:02.352 --> 19:03.813
Shouldn't you be at home getting
ready for court or something?

19:03.813 --> 19:06.686
No.
I shouldn't be here.

19:06.686 --> 19:08.818
I should be at home fixing
my daughter ice cream

19:08.818 --> 19:09.939
and reading her
"Charlotte's Web."

19:09.939 --> 19:11.531
So could you please
page Russo

19:11.531 --> 19:13.152
so I can look at the ultrasounds
and get the hell out of here?

19:13.152 --> 19:14.574
Okay.

19:14.574 --> 19:16.866
Thank you.

19:16.866 --> 19:18.908
[ Siren wails ]

19:18.908 --> 19:21.080
It's an impossible
situation.

19:21.080 --> 19:22.832
A break-up is tough enough
as it is,

19:22.832 --> 19:24.043
but with a kid
in the mix...

19:24.043 --> 19:25.495
I can't even imagine.

19:25.495 --> 19:26.876
[ Sighs ] I mean,
just because you're not

19:26.876 --> 19:28.047
the parent who gave birth
to the kid

19:28.047 --> 19:29.379
doesn't make the kid
any less yours.

19:29.379 --> 19:30.960
Biology or not,

19:30.960 --> 19:32.922
no parent ever fought
to stick around for me.

19:32.922 --> 19:35.054
[ Groans ]

19:35.054 --> 19:37.387
It was
a horrible mistake.

19:37.387 --> 19:38.638
The custody battle?

19:38.638 --> 19:39.849
Me breaking up with Kyle.

19:39.849 --> 19:41.801
-I told you that.
-Who's Kyle?

19:41.801 --> 19:43.563
He was
a once-in-a-lifetime butt.

19:43.563 --> 19:44.894
I said that, too.

19:44.894 --> 19:45.935
I'm calling him.

19:45.935 --> 19:48.308
-Ooh.
-Mm, the -- the drunk-dial.

19:48.308 --> 19:49.769
It's a bad idea.
-I'm not drunk.

19:49.769 --> 19:51.110
Hey!
Steph, look at me.

19:51.110 --> 19:53.613
You have 10 more seconds
to talk about him,

19:53.613 --> 19:55.154
and then no more Kyle talk.

19:55.154 --> 19:56.236
I said that to you.

19:56.236 --> 19:57.237
I know.

19:57.237 --> 19:59.449
10, 9...

19:59.449 --> 20:01.411
Shut up.
I'm calling him.

20:01.411 --> 20:03.623
And it is not drunk-dialing,
sir.

20:03.623 --> 20:06.085
It is
me undoing my mistake.

20:06.085 --> 20:07.787
-Okay.
-I --

20:07.787 --> 20:08.918
[ Whining ]
Give it back.

20:08.918 --> 20:09.919
No.

20:09.919 --> 20:11.591
You are a good friend.

20:11.591 --> 20:12.592
I know.

20:12.592 --> 20:16.095
♪♪

20:16.095 --> 20:18.758
So,
what were you thinking?

20:18.758 --> 20:21.261
Okay, um...

20:21.261 --> 20:22.762
When the baby's born --

20:22.762 --> 20:24.644
Wow.
Starting Day 1, huh?

20:24.644 --> 20:28.898
I would like to be in the room
for the birth.

20:28.898 --> 20:30.270
Um, so if that makes you
uncomfortable --

20:30.270 --> 20:32.652
♪ It's been 7 hour and 13 days ♪
No, not at all.

20:32.652 --> 20:34.444
-Really?
-Yeah.

20:34.444 --> 20:35.775
Yeah, I want you there.

20:35.775 --> 20:37.907
Okay. Um...
♪ Since you took
your love away ♪

20:37.907 --> 20:39.859
Well, when the baby's on
a feeding schedule,

20:39.859 --> 20:42.452
whenever that happens,
then I'm thinking weekends?

20:42.452 --> 20:44.073
You don't want to
split the week?

20:44.073 --> 20:45.575
I do. Yes.
♪ I got out every night
and sleep all day ♪

20:45.575 --> 20:46.746
But when the baby's older,

20:46.746 --> 20:48.328
we may need to switch
to every other week.

20:48.328 --> 20:50.500
I've read that that is just --
-Easier on the child.

20:50.500 --> 20:51.961
Yeah, I-I read that, too.
♪ Since you took
your love away ♪

20:51.961 --> 20:53.923
But I want Easter.
It's important to me.

20:53.923 --> 20:57.046
I go to church, and you --
-Worship the Easter Bunny.

20:57.046 --> 20:58.928
Right.

20:58.928 --> 21:00.880
Now, are we talking
Easter egg hunts

21:00.880 --> 21:02.091
or just church?
♪ Since you've been gone,
I can do whatever I want ♪

21:02.091 --> 21:03.553
Yeah, of course there will be
an Easter egg hunt.

21:03.553 --> 21:06.265
All right,
then Easter's all yours.

21:06.265 --> 21:09.058
Uh, and you can have
the Super Bowl and Halloween.

21:09.058 --> 21:10.940
Mm. Sure.

21:10.940 --> 21:13.733
Okay, now,
what about, uh, Christmas?

21:16.275 --> 21:19.198
♪ Eat my dinner
in a fancy restaurant ♪

21:19.198 --> 21:20.610
We switch off.

21:20.610 --> 21:23.993
We switch off.
We, uh, make a plan.
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

21:23.993 --> 21:25.785
We respect the plan.
♪ But nothing, nothing
can take away these blues ♪

21:25.785 --> 21:27.867
We don't fight.

21:27.867 --> 21:30.249
♪ Oh-ho ♪

21:30.249 --> 21:31.331
Yeah, we don't fight.

21:31.331 --> 21:34.253
♪ Nothing compares ♪

21:34.253 --> 21:35.335
[ Glasses clink ]

21:35.335 --> 21:36.756
♪ Nothing compares to you ♪

21:36.756 --> 21:38.177
Okay, sweetie.

21:38.177 --> 21:39.969
Yeah, no,
it's past your bedtime.

21:39.969 --> 21:41.341
Okay. Hey.
♪ Oh, baby ♪

21:41.341 --> 21:42.512
I love you.

21:42.512 --> 21:44.924
[ Meredith sighs ]

21:44.924 --> 21:46.516
Okay. No, no, no.

21:46.516 --> 21:48.728
No, I don't want to
talk to Mommy, okay?

21:48.728 --> 21:53.983
Okay, bye --
♪ It's been so lonely
without you here ♪

21:53.983 --> 21:56.436
I feel gross.
♪ I'm like a bird
without a song ♪

21:56.436 --> 21:58.398
I feel gross. Court covered me
in a layer of gross

21:58.398 --> 22:01.110
no amount of wine
can wash away.

22:02.492 --> 22:04.364
-Tequila?
-Mnh-mnh.

22:04.364 --> 22:05.244
♪ Nothin' can stop this
lonely rain for fallin' ♪

22:05.244 --> 22:06.446
You know,
you don't have to stay.

22:06.446 --> 22:07.907
I'll be fine alone
till Penny gets home.

22:07.907 --> 22:09.909
Oh.
That won't be for hours.

22:09.909 --> 22:11.290
♪ Tell me, baby,
where did I go wrong? ♪

22:11.290 --> 22:13.793
I buried her
in scut and post-ops.

22:13.793 --> 22:14.834
[ Both laugh ]

22:14.834 --> 22:15.875
I'll call you a cab.

22:15.875 --> 22:17.046
Go home and see your kids.

22:17.046 --> 22:18.758
My kids are asleep.
♪ Oh, baby ♪

22:18.758 --> 22:20.129
They're with
Maggie and Amelia.

22:20.129 --> 22:24.764
♪ I can put my arms
around every boy I see ♪

22:24.764 --> 22:26.265
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

22:26.265 --> 22:28.728
What if last night
was our last night?

22:28.728 --> 22:29.809
Stop.
Don't do that.

22:29.809 --> 22:31.681
I am doing this all wrong.

22:31.681 --> 22:33.142
♪ All my dames remind me of you,
too, girl ♪

22:33.142 --> 22:34.974
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

22:34.974 --> 22:37.236
♪ I went to the doctor ♪
Mark used to say that.

22:37.236 --> 22:39.068
♪ Guess what he told me ♪
[ Sighs ]

22:39.068 --> 22:40.359
♪ Guess what he told me ♪

22:40.359 --> 22:41.651
♪ I'm listening ♪
♪ He said, "Rosie" ♪

22:41.651 --> 22:42.862
You know...
♪ What? ♪

22:42.862 --> 22:43.783
♪ Try to have fun
no matter what you do ♪

22:43.783 --> 22:45.364
...when the kids
were babies,

22:45.364 --> 22:48.538
he used to call me all the time
when Sofia would cry

22:48.538 --> 22:50.660
or she got soap in her eye

22:50.660 --> 22:52.081
and he didn't know
what to do.
♪ Nothing compares ♪

22:52.081 --> 22:54.293
He called you?
He had two moms!
♪ No ♪

22:54.293 --> 22:56.456
♪ Nothing compares to you ♪

22:56.456 --> 22:58.708
Yeah, but the two of you
were so on top of it,

22:58.708 --> 22:59.629
he didn't want you to know.

22:59.629 --> 23:02.632
So he swore me to secrecy.

23:02.632 --> 23:04.634
♪ Ooh, my baby ♪
♪ Tenor man, play it for me ♪

23:04.634 --> 23:06.636
He would hate this.

23:06.636 --> 23:10.560
♪ I know that living with me,
baby, is sometimes hard ♪
So much.

23:10.560 --> 23:12.432
♪ Sometimes hard ♪
He would find it unacceptable.

23:12.432 --> 23:14.514
[ Sighs ]
♪ But I'm willing ♪

23:14.514 --> 23:17.356
♪ I'm willing
to give it one more try ♪

23:17.356 --> 23:19.148
♪ Please, do you know why? ♪

23:19.148 --> 23:20.189
♪ Do you know why? ♪
I lie awake every night

23:20.189 --> 23:22.151
thinking maybe I started
something I shouldn't have.

23:22.151 --> 23:25.284
♪ Nothing compares, no ♪

23:25.284 --> 23:27.447
♪ Nothing compares to you ♪

23:27.447 --> 23:28.828
I shouldn't have to choose
between the person that I love

23:28.828 --> 23:32.081
and the person I love.
♪ Oh, baby ♪

23:32.081 --> 23:34.033
♪ Every time I,
every time I say ♪

23:34.033 --> 23:36.796
I hope you don't have to.

23:36.796 --> 23:38.958
♪ Nothing compares, no ♪

23:38.958 --> 23:41.461
I tried...
not to love Penny, Mer.

23:41.461 --> 23:43.212
♪ Nothing compares to you ♪
I tried.

23:43.212 --> 23:44.544
So hard.

23:44.544 --> 23:48.257
[ Vocalizing ]

23:48.257 --> 23:49.258
[ Sighs ]

23:49.258 --> 23:51.260
I know.
This all sucks.

23:51.260 --> 23:54.263
♪♪

24:03.773 --> 24:05.274
Arizona:
Come on, Sofia, honey.

24:05.274 --> 24:06.195
You had a really good time with
her yesterday, okay?

24:06.195 --> 24:07.326
-Unh-unh.
-Yes! You did.

24:07.326 --> 24:08.778
You built forts
and it was really fun.

24:08.778 --> 24:09.779
Morning! Come on in!

24:09.779 --> 24:10.950
Hi! Here we go!

24:10.950 --> 24:12.662
I don't want to.

24:12.662 --> 24:14.283
I'm sorry. It's been
a really rough morning.

24:14.283 --> 24:15.495
She woke up really early

24:15.495 --> 24:16.666
and then she didn't
have breakfast, so --

24:16.666 --> 24:18.668
That's okay.
We will make waffles, or --

24:18.668 --> 24:20.289
I'm going with you.

24:20.289 --> 24:23.342
I -- Oh, I can't. I can't.
Mommy can't today.

24:23.342 --> 24:24.924
I'm running late, and
you're here to play with Zola,

24:24.924 --> 24:26.175
but I will be back
just as soon as I can.

24:26.175 --> 24:27.386
No.

24:27.386 --> 24:28.928
[ Sighs ] I'm sorry.

24:28.928 --> 24:30.510
I-I'm sorry.
I love you.

24:30.510 --> 24:31.681
I hate you.

24:31.681 --> 24:33.513
Okay,
let's go find Zola.

24:33.513 --> 24:34.764
She'll be fine.

24:34.764 --> 24:36.475
[ Dog barking in distance ]
[ Door closes ]

24:36.475 --> 24:38.307
Hey. How's Jenny doing?

24:38.307 --> 24:39.478
She did okay overnight,

24:39.478 --> 24:41.060
but her mean pressure
is trending down.

24:41.060 --> 24:42.812
I don't like it.
-What does Russo say?

24:42.812 --> 24:44.483
Russo says
to watch and wait,

24:44.483 --> 24:46.736
but I'm thinking about
texting Arizona.

24:46.736 --> 24:48.107
Arizona doesn't have
all the answers.

24:48.107 --> 24:49.659
She has more answers
than Russo.

24:49.659 --> 24:51.611
And you're just pissy because
she fired you as a patient.

24:51.611 --> 24:53.412
[ Scoffs ] Shut up. She's got
enough on her plate today.

24:53.412 --> 24:54.994
Okay, look.
If Russo says watch and wait,

24:54.994 --> 24:56.415
I say we watch and wait.

24:56.415 --> 24:58.207
Any evidence of fetal distress
on the monitor,

24:58.207 --> 24:59.458
just let me know, okay?

25:01.751 --> 25:05.254
Meredith:
And Dr. Torres and Sofia
couldn't possibly be any closer.

25:05.254 --> 25:07.006
Carpio:
So, you've seen them together
frequently over the years.

25:07.006 --> 25:08.047
All the time.

25:08.047 --> 25:09.468
They went to
the same daycare

25:09.468 --> 25:11.090
and now
they're at the same school.

25:11.090 --> 25:13.392
Sofia's actually at my house
right now.

25:13.392 --> 25:14.764
And what about Dr. Blake?

25:14.764 --> 25:16.806
In your estimation, how does
she get along with Sofia?

25:16.806 --> 25:18.267
Great.
Sofia loves Penny.

25:18.267 --> 25:19.729
She's a great kid
like that.

25:19.729 --> 25:22.401
She's very open to new people
as long as they're good people,

25:22.401 --> 25:24.403
and Penny
is a very good person.

25:25.775 --> 25:27.697
Thank you, Dr. Grey.

25:27.697 --> 25:29.068
It's your witness,
Ms. Gamble.

25:30.489 --> 25:34.243
You mentioned that Sofia is
at your house today, Dr. Grey.

25:34.243 --> 25:36.826
She is.
It must be nice
for you and Dr. Torres

25:36.826 --> 25:38.157
to have daughters
around the same age.

25:38.157 --> 25:39.248
And they get along,
right?

25:39.248 --> 25:40.499
It is very nice.

25:40.499 --> 25:41.921
They love playing together.

25:41.921 --> 25:42.872
So, who's watching
your daughters

25:42.872 --> 25:43.963
right now
while you're here?

25:43.963 --> 25:45.214
Their Aunt Amelia.

25:46.716 --> 25:48.798
You recently
lost your husband.

25:48.798 --> 25:49.969
Is that correct?

25:51.300 --> 25:52.842
I did.

25:52.842 --> 25:54.974
My sincerest condolences.

25:54.974 --> 25:56.806
Thank you.

25:56.806 --> 25:59.438
So,
you're a single parent.

25:59.438 --> 26:01.270
I am.

26:01.270 --> 26:03.603
And Callie's
a single parent.

26:05.234 --> 26:06.485
Is that a question,
or --

26:06.485 --> 26:08.948
So you two must
help each other out a lot --

26:08.948 --> 26:10.239
two single parents.

26:10.239 --> 26:12.321
Callie drops Sofia off
at your place sometimes

26:12.321 --> 26:14.243
when she has to work
or when she has plans

26:14.243 --> 26:17.196
or when she needs a night off.
Correct?

26:17.196 --> 26:19.578
A "night off"?

26:19.578 --> 26:21.621
Being a mom isn't a job.

26:21.621 --> 26:23.582
We don't punch in
and punch out.

26:23.582 --> 26:25.294
There are no nights off.

26:25.294 --> 26:26.666
We are both single parents.

26:26.666 --> 26:28.547
That's not a dirty word.

26:28.547 --> 26:31.921
But we do need help getting our
kids to where they need to be

26:31.921 --> 26:33.512
with all of
their limbs intact.

26:33.512 --> 26:35.474
So we lean on each other.

26:35.474 --> 26:38.097
That's not a sign of weakness
or bad parenting,

26:38.097 --> 26:39.639
if that's where
you're going with this.

26:39.639 --> 26:43.022
It takes a village,
and we have a village.

26:43.022 --> 26:45.024
-Here in Seattle.
-What?

26:45.024 --> 26:46.525
The village
you just mentioned --

26:46.525 --> 26:48.688
the seamless support system
these mothers built,

26:48.688 --> 26:50.650
this essential network.

26:50.650 --> 26:52.732
It's all here in Seattle.

26:52.732 --> 26:55.284
Sofia's friends and her school,
her teachers --

26:55.284 --> 26:57.907
her home
is here in Seattle.

26:57.907 --> 27:01.450
That's
what Sofia would be leaving.

27:01.450 --> 27:02.541
Is that
what you're saying?

27:02.541 --> 27:04.413
No. I was saying --

27:04.413 --> 27:06.585
No further questions,
Your Honor.

27:06.585 --> 27:09.628
♪♪

27:13.302 --> 27:16.215
Dr. Robbins was already
a brilliant pediatric surgeon,

27:16.215 --> 27:19.098
but since she's completed
her fellowship,

27:19.098 --> 27:20.519
I've watched her turn into

27:20.519 --> 27:23.392
one of the most renowned
fetal surgeons in the country.

27:23.392 --> 27:25.604
A child would be lucky to have
her as a role model parent.

27:27.526 --> 27:29.568
No further questions,
Your Honor.

27:34.073 --> 27:36.986
Dr. Webber, you work with
Dr. Robbins -- is that correct?

27:36.986 --> 27:38.738
Uh, yes, that's correct.

27:38.738 --> 27:41.450
Would you say there's overlap
between your specialties?

27:41.450 --> 27:42.742
Yes, there is.

27:42.742 --> 27:45.164
So, you two have gotten close
over the years.

27:45.164 --> 27:46.876
Professionally.
-We have. Yes.

27:53.672 --> 27:55.384
Are you a trivia buff?

27:55.384 --> 27:57.176
[ Sighs ]

27:57.176 --> 27:58.928
Yes.

27:58.928 --> 28:01.430
So, you and Dr. Robbins have
enjoyed trivia nights together.

28:01.430 --> 28:02.641
That's correct, yes.

28:02.641 --> 28:04.063
You go and play, drink,

28:04.063 --> 28:05.474
and flirt with women --
is that correct?

28:05.474 --> 28:08.107
No, it isn't.
I'm married and I don't drink.

28:08.107 --> 28:09.688
So Dr. Robbins did all
the drinking and flirting.

28:09.688 --> 28:10.810
You just went
for the trivia?

28:10.810 --> 28:12.021
That's
an over-simplified --

28:12.021 --> 28:13.943
It's a yes or no question,
Dr. Webber.

28:13.943 --> 28:15.274
Yes.

28:15.274 --> 28:17.737
You're good at trivia?

28:17.737 --> 28:19.368
-Sure.
-Don't be modest.

28:19.368 --> 28:22.031
How many times do you think
you and Dr. Robbins have won

28:22.031 --> 28:23.412
over the past, oh,
let's say six months?

28:23.412 --> 28:25.324
I wasn't counting.

28:25.324 --> 28:27.666
The bar was.
They kept a running tally.

28:27.666 --> 28:31.921
Does this piece of evidence,
Document 3C,

28:31.921 --> 28:34.213
refresh your recollection?

28:34.213 --> 28:37.336
♪♪

28:37.336 --> 28:40.099
You've won 25 times
in the past six months.

28:40.099 --> 28:42.972
That's 25 nights Dr. Robbins
was out drinking with you,

28:42.972 --> 28:45.014
not including
the times you lost.

28:47.016 --> 28:48.437
Where was Sofia
during those evenings?

28:48.437 --> 28:50.149
I don't know.

28:50.149 --> 28:51.650
I'm sorry. I didn't --
I didn't quite catch that.

28:51.650 --> 28:54.313
I said I wasn't privy to
her childcare schedule.

28:54.313 --> 28:56.906
I would like to introduce
into evidence Document 4C.

28:56.906 --> 28:59.028
It is a transcript
of text messages

28:59.028 --> 29:01.490
from Dr. Robbins
to Dr. Torres

29:01.490 --> 29:03.032
asking her
to take Sofia unexpectedly.

29:03.032 --> 29:05.034
[ Scoffs ] Callie and I swap
all the time.

29:05.034 --> 29:06.365
We have
very flexible schedules.

29:06.365 --> 29:08.037
Shh.

29:08.037 --> 29:09.458
Carpio:
Could you please tell the court

29:09.458 --> 29:11.290
the tally at the bottom?

29:11.290 --> 29:14.293
♪♪

29:14.293 --> 29:15.254
Dr. Webber?

29:15.254 --> 29:17.546
[ Scoffs ]

29:17.546 --> 29:19.218
-34.
-34.

29:19.218 --> 29:23.012
She asked Dr. Torres to
switch with her 34 times.

29:23.012 --> 29:25.764
We know she was out with you
at least 25 times.

29:25.764 --> 29:27.766
And that's in addition to
the previously mentioned

29:27.766 --> 29:30.689
92 times Dr. Robbins
was unavailable

29:30.689 --> 29:33.522
to parent her own child
due to her professional demands.

29:33.522 --> 29:37.106
Now, let's just pause and think
about this for a minute.

29:37.106 --> 29:40.279
There are only 180 days
in six months' time,

29:40.279 --> 29:43.162
and so far, we've counted
approximately 150 times

29:43.162 --> 29:45.164
in which Dr. Robbins
shirked her duties.

29:45.164 --> 29:46.866
150 out of 180.

29:46.866 --> 29:48.617
Objection.
Badgering the witness.

29:48.617 --> 29:50.459
Calls for speculation.

29:50.459 --> 29:51.620
Sustained.

29:51.620 --> 29:54.043
Your Honor, we'd like to
request a short recess.

29:54.043 --> 29:55.875
[ Gavel bangs ]

30:05.975 --> 30:07.096
So, Callie's okay
slut-shaming me now?

30:07.096 --> 30:08.517
Don't let them rattle you.

30:08.517 --> 30:09.728
They're making it sound like
a working mom is a bad mom.

30:09.728 --> 30:10.689
I mean, we just lost in there,
right?

30:10.689 --> 30:11.891
'Cause they made me sound like

30:11.891 --> 30:14.353
I was a selfish, irresponsible,
sex-crazed --

30:14.353 --> 30:15.104
-Arizona.
-I don't --

30:15.104 --> 30:16.856
Stop.

30:16.856 --> 30:18.607
You have your chance
right now.

30:18.607 --> 30:20.359
They tried to
rewrite the story.

30:20.359 --> 30:22.111
Now's your chance
to set it straight.

30:22.111 --> 30:25.404
You need to get up there,
tell them the truth.

30:25.404 --> 30:26.785
Judge Kane is smart.

30:26.785 --> 30:28.948
She'll know the truth
when she hears it.

30:28.948 --> 30:31.540
You tell the truth,
and you will win this.

30:31.540 --> 30:34.003
♪♪

30:34.003 --> 30:36.715
Carpio: When Sofia was born,
how did that day start for you?

30:36.715 --> 30:38.667
[ Sighs ]

30:38.667 --> 30:40.839
I was in a car accident.

30:42.922 --> 30:45.764
Can you tell us what you
remember about the accident?

30:45.764 --> 30:50.389
I don't remember much,
but I remember --

30:50.389 --> 30:54.934
I remember waking up
on the hood of the car

30:54.934 --> 30:58.817
and I was covered in glass.

30:58.817 --> 31:01.860
I was, um, barely --

31:01.860 --> 31:04.323
I'm so sorry.

31:04.323 --> 31:07.116
Take all the time you need.

31:07.116 --> 31:09.909
♪♪

31:16.125 --> 31:18.127
[ Clears throat ]

31:18.127 --> 31:21.300
I was barely conscious,
um,

31:21.300 --> 31:24.924
and the only thing that I could
feel was just pain all over.

31:27.056 --> 31:30.769
I could have died
on the hood of that car.

31:30.769 --> 31:33.772
[ Voice breaking ]
And I wanted to give up.

31:33.772 --> 31:38.727
But...I couldn't because
I was pregnant with Sofia.

31:40.569 --> 31:44.653
And if I died...she died.

31:44.653 --> 31:50.239
So...I had to fight...

31:50.239 --> 31:53.332
to stay alive,
for my daughter's sake.

31:56.996 --> 31:59.798
Being a mother is the reason
I'm still alive today.

32:01.710 --> 32:03.922
[ Sniffles ]

32:03.922 --> 32:05.804
[ Sighs ]

32:05.804 --> 32:08.847
♪♪

32:10.009 --> 32:11.600
[ Sniffles ]

32:11.600 --> 32:12.681
[ Sighs ]

32:12.681 --> 32:15.814
[ Monitor beeping ]

32:15.814 --> 32:18.057
Jenny,
your BP's borderline low,

32:18.057 --> 32:20.609
but otherwise,
your cardiac evaluation is good.

32:20.609 --> 32:22.061
So,
she's cleared for surgery.

32:22.061 --> 32:24.403
-Surgery. What surgery?
-What happened?

32:24.403 --> 32:26.986
Dr. Russo says
we have to deliver.

32:26.986 --> 32:28.867
Jenny's still leaking
amniotic fluid,

32:28.867 --> 32:30.489
which means
we're out of time.

32:30.489 --> 32:32.701
We need to do a C-section,
deliver this baby.

32:32.701 --> 32:34.283
Right now?
I-It's too early, right?

32:34.283 --> 32:37.166
It's not ideal,
but there may be no choice.

32:37.166 --> 32:38.877
Please don't.
Not yet.

32:38.877 --> 32:40.129
I don't want my baby to die.

32:40.129 --> 32:42.001
Honey, everything
is gonna be fine.

32:42.001 --> 32:43.632
Can I see you outside?

32:43.632 --> 32:45.884
♪♪

32:48.217 --> 32:50.179
If that baby
comes out now --

32:50.179 --> 32:52.011
It has to.

32:52.011 --> 32:53.392
The fetal heart rate's
already showing

32:53.392 --> 32:54.683
decreased variability.

32:54.683 --> 32:56.355
Well, what can we do?

32:56.355 --> 32:58.517
I can deliver, then you do
what you can for the baby.

32:58.517 --> 33:01.190
It's hard to keep those babies
alive. The odds suck.

33:01.190 --> 33:03.312
Compromised lungs,
high risk of brain bleeds.

33:03.312 --> 33:05.364
It's the only option left.

33:05.364 --> 33:06.695
It's what we're doing.

33:08.907 --> 33:10.909
So,
I just lied to my daughter,

33:10.909 --> 33:12.371
and I will
go back in there

33:12.371 --> 33:14.663
and keep telling her that
she'll be okay no matter what,

33:14.663 --> 33:16.875
but to do that, I need to know
that you have done

33:16.875 --> 33:19.328
everything in your power
to make this okay.

33:19.328 --> 33:20.579
Can you tell me that?

33:20.579 --> 33:22.881
Tell me that you have done
everything you can

33:22.881 --> 33:25.214
to keep my baby
and grandchild alive.

33:26.675 --> 33:29.588
[ Door opens, closes ]

33:29.588 --> 33:31.630
Robbins wouldn't deliver.

33:31.630 --> 33:33.432
Do you have
another option?

33:35.054 --> 33:36.555
[ Sighs ]

33:36.555 --> 33:37.936
Then I'll see you in surgery.

33:39.558 --> 33:41.230
Is Robbins an option?

33:41.230 --> 33:43.232
No.

33:43.232 --> 33:46.275
♪♪

33:51.490 --> 33:54.203
Carpio: Dr. Robbins,
you were with Dr. Torres

33:54.203 --> 33:55.954
before she was pregnant.
-Yes.

33:55.954 --> 33:57.996
Were you together when
she got pregnant?
No.

33:57.996 --> 33:59.458
So her pregnancy was not
an agreement

33:59.458 --> 34:02.040
you entered into together,
correct?
No.

34:02.040 --> 34:03.502
It was an agreement
she entered into

34:03.502 --> 34:04.833
with Dr. Mark Sloan,
correct?

34:04.833 --> 34:06.375
They agreed after the fact,

34:06.375 --> 34:08.087
but, yes,
Mark was Sofia's father.

34:08.087 --> 34:09.628
Callie and I were together.

34:09.628 --> 34:11.380
We were a couple
before the pregnancy

34:11.380 --> 34:13.302
and then after
Sofia was conceived.

34:13.302 --> 34:15.934
So, you became part of the
parenting plan later, correct?

34:15.934 --> 34:17.976
[ Cellphone rings ]
Just to be clear,

34:17.976 --> 34:20.729
Dr. Sloan and Dr. Torres
were Sofia's parents

34:20.729 --> 34:22.391
and then you came around.

34:22.391 --> 34:23.642
No,
I didn't "come around."

34:23.642 --> 34:25.274
I'm Sofia's mother.
I legally adopted her.

34:25.274 --> 34:27.236
She doesn't
want to go there.

34:27.236 --> 34:28.237
No, she doesn't.

34:28.237 --> 34:30.189
Her last names
are Sloan and Torres.

34:30.189 --> 34:31.610
I'm gonna have to stop you
before you continue

34:31.610 --> 34:33.402
for your own sake.

34:33.402 --> 34:35.284
You're not going to imply that
I'm any less Sofia's mother

34:35.284 --> 34:36.865
because we don't
share the same DNA.

34:36.865 --> 34:38.907
[ Cellphone rings ]
Dr. Robbins, excuse me.

34:38.907 --> 34:40.249
Because that would be offensive.
It would be offensive

34:40.249 --> 34:42.411
to anyone in the room
who has an adopted child

34:42.411 --> 34:44.873
or is an adopted child,
and for you to say that --

34:44.873 --> 34:47.796
-Dr. Robbins --
-I chose to be Sofia's mother!

34:47.796 --> 34:50.589
It did not fall into my lap.

34:52.010 --> 34:54.553
There was a choice,
and I could stay or I could run,

34:54.553 --> 34:57.176
and I chose motherhood.

34:57.176 --> 34:59.348
And it was the best choice
that I ever made.

34:59.348 --> 35:02.060
[ Cellphone rings ]

35:02.060 --> 35:03.892
[ Sighs ]
I'm -- I'm -- I'm so sorry.

35:03.892 --> 35:06.645
I'm a doctor, and I-I have to
answer my phone, so I'm sorry.

35:06.645 --> 35:09.278
I'm -- I'm so sorry.

35:09.278 --> 35:12.401
♪♪

35:12.401 --> 35:14.072
Thank you.

35:16.905 --> 35:18.367
[ Sighs ]

35:18.367 --> 35:20.199
Somewhere
more important to be?

35:21.950 --> 35:22.951
Actually, yes.

35:22.951 --> 35:24.833
Excuse me?

35:24.833 --> 35:27.085
I'm sorry.

35:27.085 --> 35:29.338
I'm so sorry.

35:29.338 --> 35:32.130
♪♪

35:38.096 --> 35:41.260
[ Sighs ]

35:43.432 --> 35:48.106
I love my child,
and I want her with me,

35:48.106 --> 35:51.570
but I know that,
no matter how this ends,

35:51.570 --> 35:55.654
she'll survive.

35:55.654 --> 35:58.987
She'll be healthy and safe

35:58.987 --> 36:01.119
and well-taken care of
and loved.

36:01.119 --> 36:04.993
Because...

36:04.993 --> 36:07.085
we are her mothers.

36:07.085 --> 36:09.878
♪♪

36:13.292 --> 36:16.134
But there's a child at the
hospital who will not survive

36:16.134 --> 36:20.389
unless I am there,
so I have to --

36:20.389 --> 36:21.430
I have to --
I have to go.

36:21.430 --> 36:24.473
♪♪

36:34.192 --> 36:35.614
[ Sighs ]

36:45.914 --> 36:47.246
Russo:
I am through the uterine wall.

36:47.246 --> 36:48.787
More suction, please.

36:48.787 --> 36:51.129
Vitals are holding.

36:51.129 --> 36:53.001
Why isn't he stopping?
Did you ask him to stop?

36:53.001 --> 36:54.503
Yes. But he's insisting
on taking the baby out.

36:54.503 --> 36:55.834
-Is he into the uterus?
-Yes.

36:55.834 --> 36:57.596
-Well, did he cut the cord?
-No, but he's close.

36:57.596 --> 36:58.797
Tell him not to.
Damn it!

36:58.797 --> 36:59.838
I did.

37:03.512 --> 37:04.643
[ Sighs ]
Okay, everyone.

37:04.643 --> 37:06.305
Change of plans.

37:06.305 --> 37:08.307
Dr. Russo, please stop
what you're doing.
Excuse me?

37:08.307 --> 37:09.728
Hi, Tara.
Hi, Jenny.

37:09.728 --> 37:11.610
You're doing great, okay?
Hey, Karev.

37:11.610 --> 37:13.021
-Cord's intact.
-Beautiful.

37:13.021 --> 37:14.313
Dr. Russo. I said stop.
Now, please.

37:14.313 --> 37:16.525
Robbins, I've almost completed
the C-section.

